<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="253" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,628,2059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,465,1780,1806]" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">Conservation status:—</emphasis>
According to IUCN criteria (2017), 
<taxonomicName box="[875,1007,1780,1806]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Microchilus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="253" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dasilvae">
<emphasis box="[875,1007,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">M. dasilvae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
falls under Data Deficient (DD). More studies are necessary to locate more populations and estimate the number of mature individuals. The area where the species was discovered suffers from anthropological disturbance, including real estate pressure, making the species naturally threatened due to habitat loss.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="256" pageId="1" pageNumber="253" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,628,2059]" lastBlockId="2.[136,1452,158,221]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="254" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,489,1924,1950]" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">Taxonomic discussion:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[489,725,1924,1950]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Microchilus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="253" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dasilvae">
<emphasis box="[489,725,1924,1950]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">Microchilus dasilvae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Reichenbach 1873: 177) Smidt et al. (2021: 339)" authorityName="Smidt et al." authorityPageNumber="339" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Reichenbach" baseAuthorityPageNumber="177" baseAuthorityYear="1873" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Microchilus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="253" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decorus">
<emphasis box="[882,1010,1924,1950]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">M. decorus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Reichenbach, H. G." box="[1027,1299,1924,1950]" pageId="1" pageNumber="253" refId="ref3531" refString="Reichenbach, H. G. (1873) New Garden Plants. The Gardeners' Chronicle &amp; Agricultural Gazette." type="book" year="1873">Reichenbach 1873: 177</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Smidt, E. C. &amp; Salazar, G. A. &amp; Mauad, A. V. S. R. &amp; Engels, M. E. &amp; Viruel, J. &amp; Clements, M. &amp; Perez, I. J. &amp; Chase, M. W." pageId="1" pageNumber="253" pagination="322 - 349" refId="ref3607" refString="Smidt, E. C., Salazar, G. A., Mauad, A. V. S. R., Engels, M. E., Viruel, J., Clements, M., Perez, I. J. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2021) An Indomalesian origin in the Miocene for the diphyletic New World jewel orchids (Goodyerinae, Orchidoideae): molecular dating and biogeographic analyses document non-monophyly of the Neotropical genera. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 197: 322 - 349. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / botlinnean / boab 028" type="journal article" year="2021">
Smidt 
<emphasis box="[1393,1452,1924,1950]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">et al.</emphasis>
(2021: 339)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[283,367,1960,1986]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,224,159,183]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison between Microchilus dasilvae and related species." pageId="1" pageNumber="253">Table 1</tableCitation>
) due to the habit (small plants, up to 
<quantity box="[793,863,1960,1987]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="253" unit="cm" value="35.0">35 cm</quantity>
tall, and leaves up to about 
<quantity box="[1182,1287,1960,1987]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.75" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="253" unit="cm" value="6.75" valueMax="7.5" valueMin="6.0">6–7.5 cm</quantity>
in length) and floral display with stained sepals and mesochile with acute lateral lobes. It can be distinguished by the yellow (
<emphasis box="[1421,1451,1997,2022]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">vs.</emphasis>
white) mesochile and the broad-oval epichile about the same width as mesochile (
<emphasis box="[1048,1078,2033,2058]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="253">vs.</emphasis>
oblanceolate to narrow elliptical, proportionately narrower than mesochile). The complete illustration of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smidt et al." authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Reichenbach" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[932,1058,158,184]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Microchilus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="254" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decorus">
<emphasis box="[932,1058,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="254">M. decorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be consulted in 
<bibRefCitation author="Sprunger, S. &amp; Cribb, P. &amp; Tosacano de Brito, A. L. V." pageId="2" pageNumber="254" refId="ref3721" refString="Sprunger, S., Cribb, P. &amp; Tosacano de Brito, A. L. V. (1996) Joao Bradosa Rodrigues Iconografia des Orchidees do Bresil. V 1: The illustrations. Friedrich Reinhardt Verlag, Basle. 540 pp." type="book" year="1996">
Sprunger 
<emphasis box="[1396,1452,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="254">et al.</emphasis>
(1996
</bibRefCitation>
: t. 136), as 
<taxonomicName authority="Barbosa Rodrigues (1882: 290)" authorityName="Barbosa Rodrigues" authorityPageNumber="290" authorityYear="1882" box="[334,888,194,220]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Physurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="254" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[334,526,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="254">Physurus bicolor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Barbosa Rodrigues, J." box="[533,888,194,220]" pageId="2" pageNumber="254" refId="ref2520" refString="Barbosa Rodrigues, J. (1882) Genera et species Orchidacearum novarum II. Sebastianopolis, Rio de Janeiro. Typografia Nacional. 295 pp." type="book" year="1882">Barbosa Rodrigues (1882: 290)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
