<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1591,1833]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">
Additionally, 
<taxonomicName box="[348,483,1591,1617]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Microchilus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dasilvae">
<emphasis box="[348,483,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">M. dasilvae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Barbosa Rodrigues 1882: 291) Smidt et al. (2021: 342)" authorityName="Smidt et al." authorityPageNumber="342" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Barbosa Rodrigues" baseAuthorityPageNumber="291" baseAuthorityYear="1882" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Microchilus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="metallescens">
<emphasis box="[650,835,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">M. metallescens</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Barbosa Rodrigues, J." box="[855,1206,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" refId="ref2520" refString="Barbosa Rodrigues, J. (1882) Genera et species Orchidacearum novarum II. Sebastianopolis, Rio de Janeiro. Typografia Nacional. 295 pp." type="book" year="1882">Barbosa Rodrigues 1882: 291</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Smidt, E. C. &amp; Salazar, G. A. &amp; Mauad, A. V. S. R. &amp; Engels, M. E. &amp; Viruel, J. &amp; Clements, M. &amp; Perez, I. J. &amp; Chase, M. W." pageId="4" pageNumber="256" pagination="322 - 349" refId="ref3607" refString="Smidt, E. C., Salazar, G. A., Mauad, A. V. S. R., Engels, M. E., Viruel, J., Clements, M., Perez, I. J. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2021) An Indomalesian origin in the Miocene for the diphyletic New World jewel orchids (Goodyerinae, Orchidoideae): molecular dating and biogeographic analyses document non-monophyly of the Neotropical genera. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 197: 322 - 349. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / botlinnean / boab 028" type="journal article" year="2021">
Smidt 
<emphasis box="[1305,1367,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">et al.</emphasis>
(2021: 342)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[205,291,1627,1653]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,224,159,183]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison between Microchilus dasilvae and related species." pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Table 1</tableCitation>
) due to the habit and floral display with stained sepals and white lip with yellow mesochile. It can be distinguished from this one by the narrow-elliptical and sub-falcated petals, slightly asymmetrical (
<emphasis box="[1303,1333,1664,1689]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">vs.</emphasis>
ovate and symmetrical); lip with mesochile with acute lateral lobes (
<emphasis box="[782,812,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">vs.</emphasis>
rounded); broad-ovate epichile with apiculate and obtuse apex (
<emphasis box="[210,240,1736,1761]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">vs.</emphasis>
oblong, non-apiculate obtuse apex); sepals with bilinear central longitudinal macula (
<emphasis box="[1252,1283,1736,1761]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">vs.</emphasis>
longitudinally trilinear macula). The complete illustration of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smidt et al." authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Barbosa Rodrigues" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[667,849,1771,1797]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Microchilus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="metallescens">
<emphasis box="[667,849,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">M. metallescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be consulted in 
<bibRefCitation author="Sprunger, S. &amp; Cribb, P. &amp; Tosacano de Brito, A. L. V." box="[1089,1401,1771,1798]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" refId="ref3721" refString="Sprunger, S., Cribb, P. &amp; Tosacano de Brito, A. L. V. (1996) Joao Bradosa Rodrigues Iconografia des Orchidees do Bresil. V 1: The illustrations. Friedrich Reinhardt Verlag, Basle. 540 pp." type="book" year="1996">
Sprunger 
<emphasis box="[1201,1259,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">et al.</emphasis>
(1996: 135)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
